headline.main: UPSET IN LIBYA SHOWS WOES OF A DESERT WAR; Supply Problem Constant, and British Are Expected to Solve It First

lead_paragraph: CAIRO, Egypt, Jan. 31 -- The capture of Bengazi may have a pleasant sound to German ears, but that little seaport is not the gateway to Cyrenaica. Field Marshal Erwin Rommel's drive into the edge of the Jebel el-Achdar, or Green Mountain, region thus far has been most successful because of a series of circumstances that worked in favor of the Axis forces.
abstract: Brit-Axis warfare in Libya discussed; map
